# .dev.vars.example — local Worker secrets for `wrangler dev`
#
# Copy this file to `.dev.vars` (gitignored) to supply Worker *secrets* during
# local `wrangler dev`. Format is dotenv-style KEY=value, one per line.
#
# There are NO Worker secrets today — this is a template for when a backend is
# added. Rules (see the "Secrets" section of README.md / CLAUDE.md):
#   - Secrets ONLY. Public, non-secret per-env config (APP_ENV, API_BASE_URL,
#     WS_URL) lives in `vars` in wrangler.jsonc — NOT here, and is NOT a secret.
#   - In deployed envs, set the same keys with:
#       wrangler secret put <NAME> --env dev|uat|prod
#   - Never commit `.dev.vars`; never put a secret in `vars` in wrangler.jsonc
#     (those values are world-readable).
#
# Example — uncomment and fill in when a backend needs them:
# EXCHANGE_API_KEY=""
# EXCHANGE_API_SECRET=""
